[{"name":"Luke","meanings":["Middle English vernacular form of   Lucas  , Latin form of the post-classical Greek name <i>Loukas</i> ‘man from Lucania’. This owes its perennial popularity throughout Christian Europe to the fact that, from the 2nd century onwards, the third gospel in the New Testament has been ascribed to the Lucas or Luke mentioned at various places in Acts and in the Epistles. Little is known about him beyond the facts that he was a doctor, a Gentile, and a friend and convert of St Paul. The name was borne by the character  Luke Skywalker  in the film Star Wars (  1977 ), and rose sharply in popularity in the 1990s."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"John Lucas AttYarde was born in 1140, in England, United Kingdom as the son of Roger Lucas AttYarde. He had at least 1 son with Eustacia de Courtenay. He died in 1215, in his hometown, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1140–1215":"1140–1215","1158–1237":"1158–1237","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1100–1144":"1100–1144","1215":"1215","1237":"1237","1158":"1158","1144":"1144","1100":"1100","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1140–1215":"1140–1215","1158–1237":"1158–1237","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1100–1144":"1100–1144","1215":"1215","1237":"1237","1158":"1158","1144":"1144","1100":"1100","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1140–1215":"1140–1215","1158–1237":"1158–1237","1175–Male":"1175–Décédé","1100–1144":"1100–1144","1215":"1215","1237":"1237","1158":"1158","1144":"1144","1100":"1100","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John Lucas AttYarde est né en 1140, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Roger Lucas AttYarde. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Eustaci